{{Quote|What am I looking at here?''"<br />"''An old crime boss called Nirama had his hideout here, back during the Clone Wars. This whole belt saw a lot of action back then. It's been deserted for maybe twenty years.|[[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Perla]]|<ref name="SW11">[[Star Wars (2013) 11|''Star Wars'' (2013) 11]]</ref>}}
The '''Cularin asteroid belt''' was a thin [[Asteroid field/Legends|asteroid belt]] in the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]]. Its [[Asteroid/Legends|asteroids]] were the remnants of [[Oblis]], the [[Jungle/Legends|jungle]] [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] of the [[Oblee]]. The asteroid belt laid between the orbits of [[Almas]] and [[Genarius]]. One of the stranger asteroids in the belt was known as the [[Crystal Snare]], a remnant of the large [[Crystal/Legends|crystal]] deposits in Oblis.<ref name="LFC" />

The Cularin asteroid belt was used as a hiding place by [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]] working for [[Nirama]]. [[Organization|Nirama's criminal organization]] itself was based on the [[Nirama's public asteroid|largest asteroid]], over 400 [[Kilometer/Legends|kilometers]] in diameter.<ref name="LFC" /> He also controlled other asteroids, including repair station [[Darkside (space station)|Darkside]], which received its name for being always in the shadow of other, bigger asteroids.<ref name="MW" />

It was also used as a hiding place and ambush point for groups of [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]], in the other part of the belt. Ships had to leave [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] to pass further in-system, which made it an ideal place for the pirates to prey.<ref name="LFC" />

==History==
[[File:Cularin_asteroid_belt.jpg|left|thumb|Cularin asteroid belt]]
At some point, the [[Czerka Arms/Legends|Czerka Mining Corporation]] established a [[Mining/Legends|mining]] outpost, [[CMC-3]], there.<ref name="TR" />

In [[188 BBY]], former [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Kibh Jeen]], who had fallen to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] due to the [[Almas Sith fortress]], used his mind powers to control the pirates in the asteroid belt and to attract other minions, creating an army that he would use for seven years in the [[Dark Jedi Conflict]]: Jeen and his troops, based in the asteroid belt, attacked the planets and the transports in the systems, and disappeared among the asteroids so that no-one could find them. Jeen was eventually killed by a local, Jedi-led armada, but the pirate presence remained in the belt.<ref name="LFC" />

In [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]], Colonel [[Jir Tramsig]], a [[Thaereian military|Thaereian]] officer assigned to protect Cularin system, reacted to the pirate ambushes on civilian ships, by sending military cruisers through that same route; in one ambush, his cruiser destroyed five pirate ships, and discouraged the tactic among the pirates.<ref name="LFC" />

In [[31 BBY/Legends|31 BBY]], the [[Blood Raptors]] organized a race through the tunnels of [[Eskaron]]. The first racer to leave the moon could choose the path for the reminder of the race: Either go through the Cularin asteroid belt and back, and then to the starting point, [[Tolea Biqua]]; or visit the dangerous [[Nub Saar]] before returning to Tolea Biqua. Expert Raptor racer [[Gael Kinner]] preferred the asteroid belt.<ref name="POB">{{LivingForce|The Price of Business}}</ref>

Soon afterwards, [[The Cell]], a faction of Nirama's organization that conspired against him, wrestled with Nirama for the control of some strategic asteroids, including the space station [[Darkside (space station)|Darkside]] and the main weapon storage facility [[Rothe Gate]]. Nirama eventually defeated the rebellion.<ref name="MW" /><ref name="UW" />

One local pirate gang known as the [[Red Fury Brotherhood/Legends|Red Fury Brotherhood]] had its base in asteroid [[L-7]], although most of the gang almost evacuated L-7 annually to go to the [[SoroSuub Corporation/Legends|SoroSuub]] party of the city of [[Tolea Biqua]], in [[Genarius]].<ref name="ItSC" />

Around 31 BBY, Nirama's agent [[Len Markus]] obtained a [[Sith artifact/Legends|Sith artifact]] called [[Darkstaff]] in the Cularin asteroid belt and attempted to leave the system with it. One decade later, Markus's agent [[Phylus Mon]], who was holding the Darkstaff, tried to hide his ship, ''[[Animiasma]]'', in the belt. The Darkstaff then tried to modify [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] around it to its image; however, it only managed to turn the ship, and not the belt, into a [[Vergence/Legends|dark side nexus]].<ref name="AMA">{{LivingForce|A Mon Alone}}</ref>

[[Scout/Legends|Explorer]] [[Jag Murrock]] discovered [[Adegan crystal/Legends|Adegan crystal]] extracts in parts of the Cularin asteroid belt around [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].

